@clubbable

What's the impact of this? Were you able to change the state of the report or actually make it "undisclosed" again? Just because you are seeing a `200 OK` response does not necessarily mean that any action is actually being executed in the backend.

Also, from the video it is clear that you are executing the request using the sessions/cookies from the original reporter. When you request disclosure of a report, you can cancel it. On this case, I understand that the disclosure was already fulfilled but it would be natural to receive a `200 OK` response if the user had that privilege before.

